direction: right

*.style.border-radius: 8
*.style.font-size: 13
*.style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
*.style.stroke: "#333333"

# --- Entry ---

entry: |md
  **/strategy-push**

  - <RHAISTRAT-NNNN>
  - needs-attention only
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Pre-conditions ---

read-local: |md
  **Read local file**

  - local/strat-tasks/*.md
  - verify workflow: local
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

fetch-labels: |md
  **Fetch labels (Jira)**

  - fetch_issue.py
  - --fields labels
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}

guard: |md
  **Guard checks**

  - has rubric-pass?
  - missing needs-attention?
  - no local file?
| {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Stop branch ---

stop: |md
  **Stop + advise**

  - use /strategy-signoff
  - or run /strategy-pull first
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Push branch ---

push-content: |md
  **Push content**

  - push_strategy.py
  - Jira ## Strategy section
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}

remove-label: |md
  **Remove needs-attention**

  - lets CI re-process
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

advise: |md
  **Advise**

  - resubmitted
  - CI re-evaluates next run
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Flow ---

entry -> read-local
read-local -> fetch-labels
fetch-labels -> guard

guard -> stop: "guard fails"
guard -> push-content: "needs-attention ✓"

push-content -> remove-label
remove-label -> advise
